Establishes requirements for providers of algorithmic recommendation services, including to: 

Optimize algorithms for positive societal impact; 

Establish management systems and technical measures for algorithm examination, ethics review, user registration, information dissemination review, security monitoring, incident response, data protection, and fraud prevention; 

Conduct regular assessments of algorithms, models, data and application outcomes; strengthen information security management and unlawful/harmful information identification; 

Consider tactics to avoid user harms; prohibit dissemination of misinformation; 

Ban false account registration, trading, manipulation and anti-competitive practices; specify  requirements for services targeting minors, the elderly, workers and consumers; 

Mandate complaint handling processes; 

Establish graded/categorized algorithm management system and filing procedures; 

Authorize security assessments and inspections by regulators; and 

Specify legal liabilities and penalties for violations.

Establishes Department of Defense policy on the development and use of autonomous and semi-autonomous weapons systems, including armed platforms that are remotely operated or operated by onboard personnel. Those policies include:

(a) Rigorous testing and evaluation requirements that must be met before a weapons system is deployed, including testing designed to ensure that weapons systems operate as intended even when subject to actions from adversaries;

(b) Requirements that humans be able to intervene should weapons systems begin to operate in unintended ways;

(c) Guidelines for the use of autonomous weapons systems designed to mitigate the probability and consequences of weapons systems acting in unintended ways;

(c) Cybersecurity requirements; and

(d) The formation of a new Autonomous Weapons System Working Group to guide the development and implementation of policy on autonomous weapons systems.
